			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="Activity 5: Brainstorming actions">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="In this activity workshop participants break into small groups to brainstorm and categorize actions to help solve the problems laid out in the how might we... so that statements.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Why do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="Brainstorming together with community members helps generate a wide range of possible actions. At this stage be open to all kinds of actions, without considering feasibility - you'll discuss that in the next activity.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="How to do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Each group should have a facilitator, notetaker, one or more easel pads, sticky notes and dots, markers, ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="template"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Ch5_Identifying_Actions_Template.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=", and one or two how might we... so that statements.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Present the how might we...so that statements and how you came up with them.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Each group should take one how might we statement and identify at least 8 potential actions to address them.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Start with a few minutes for people to brainstorm individually, then share with the group and list on a white board or flip chart.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Categorize the actions using dots, sticky groupings, or markers. Categories you might consider using: Who would be involved with making a decision, what type of action is it, who would benefit the most.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Add new actions &amp; tweak actions. Take 5 - 10 minutes to brainstorm and record additional actions that came to mind, or modifications that might help the proposed actions expand their potential benefits.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Discussion. In the remaining time, discuss the groups' reactions and opinions.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
